It's Cash only, so be prepared.

This restaurant serves typical Ecuadorian dishes as well as lunches. The lunches are served Mon-Fri, and include a choice of soup, entree, and drink for a great price. The food is delicious, and portions are generous. They would definitely benefit from having a few more servers, as this place is always busy. The interior is not the nicest I've seen, but if the food is delicious, who cares?

I love their food the reason why I am giving them 3 Stars is because I have gone there now a few times and as far as Seafood they are the Best around for typical Ecuadorian seafood but I didn't give them a 5 star due to their schedule saying closes at 10pm and they close at 9pm.Twice I have gone and twice there where people inside and door was locked so as a patron I took my $$$$ to next nearest Ecuadorian Restaurant Called Sol De Quito I highly recommend them they are open late and during week sell the daily special called Merienda till 10pm and it's a full meal for just $8. Tax included soup(Daily various types) and rice with choice(pork,meat, seafood) as a second plate and juice included.Weekends which is when I last went they don't have the Daily special but place was very bright clean and good service.P.S. I am Ecuadorian Born raised here in NYC and I tried all the Ecuadorian Restaurants in East Coast.

First of all the tablecloths are stained, chairs have mold and the padding has holes. In addition the owner is gross and is very money hungry. I requested a Ceviche which is a cold plate with shrimps for $18.00 and a mixed Ceviche which consisted of fish, calamari, shrimp for $19.00. This was for take out when I check the bag to make sure I got what I paid for the container is not even half of the other order.  Not to mention that prior to placing the order I requested to know the portion and the owner said it was the big container for both of them. I went and asked them why am I getting this small container and the owner replied oh that order comes in that portion. I requested my money back and the owner even asked me to give him back the spicy sauce that came with my order and the rice. Folks, please don't even think of going to this horrible apocalyptic place.
